name: proto 1
description: cnc'ed from a solid block of high grade Dura-Bar ductile iron this machine has been pulled and stretched to an all new geometry to provide the strongest possible push for large needle groupings.  my shaders will run a 15 through a 35 all day.  hand wrapped coils, hand cut springs and a custom heated finish complete the overall look and feel of these massive machines.  guaranteed to survive the apocalypse with shaders running around 104 @ 6.5v  51%duty  and a liner around 137 @ 6.5v  47%duty.  guaranteed for the life of me or the machine.  thanks, Scott LaMadline (breadwinnerirons)
